com.beaglebuddy.id3.v24.frame_body

Class ID3v24FrameBodySynchronizedTempoCodes

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.beaglebuddy.util.Utility
      • com.beaglebuddy.id3.v24.frame_body.ID3v24FrameBodyUtility
        • com.beaglebuddy.id3.v24.frame_body.ID3v24FrameBody
          • com.beaglebuddy.id3.v24.frame_body.ID3v24FrameBodySynchronizedTempoCodes

  • public class ID3v24FrameBodySynchronizedTempoCodes
extends ID3v24FrameBody

    A synchronized tempo codes frame body is associated with an ID3v2.4 SYTC frame which is used to specify tempo changes in the .mp3 song. A tempo is specified as the metronome setting, ie, the number of beats per minute. Its range is from 2 - 510 bpm. The synchronized tempo codes frame body contains the following fields:

    Synchronized Tempo Codes Frame Body Fields
     FieldDescription
    1. time stamp formatunits of the time stamp field in the tempo changes.
    2. tempoChanges list of tempo changes within the .mp3 song.

    There may be only one synchronized tempo codes frame in an ID3v2.4 tag.

    See Also:
    ID3v24Frame, ID3 tag version 2.4.0 standard, wikipedia history of ID3 tags
